# Trivy Vulnerability Ignore File
# =============================================================================
# Document acceptable security risks that have been reviewed and deemed low impact
# 
# Format: CVE-ID # Justification
# Review this file monthly and remove entries when patches are available

# Alpine Package CVEs - Review Weekly
# -------------------------------------
# Note: Some CVEs may be false positives or affect unused features
# Always verify with: trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL <image>

# Example entries (remove after verification):
# CVE-2024-XXXXX # Low severity, affects unused curl feature, no exploit available
# CVE-2024-XXXXX # False positive, not applicable to our Node.js usage

# OpenSSL CVEs
# ------------
# We explicitly install latest libcrypto3 and libssl3 in Dockerfiles
# Any remaining CVEs should be documented here with mitigation notes

# Node.js CVEs  
# ------------
# Using Node.js 20.11.1 LTS with security patches
# Document any CVEs from upstream Node.js that are accepted

# npm/pnpm CVEs
# -------------
# Production images don't include npm/pnpm, only node binary
# Development stage CVEs are not deployed to production

# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT: Do not add CVEs here without:
# 1. Verifying the CVE applies to our usage
# 2. Documenting why it's acceptable or mitigated
# 3. Adding a review date and owner
# 4. Getting security team approval for HIGH/CRITICAL CVEs
# =============================================================================
